---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'what-is-covered', text: 'What\'s Covered', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Plan Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'treatment-types', text: 'Treatment Types', level: 2 },
  { id: 'considerations', text: 'Key Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Wellness Insurance', href: '/best/wellness-insurance' },
  { title: 'Outpatient Insurance', href: '/best/outpatient-insurance' },
  { title: 'Chronic Condition Insurance', href: '/best/chronic-condition-insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'altMedicine', header: 'Alt Medicine' },
  { key: 'chiropractic', header: 'Chiropractic' },
  { key: 'acupuncture', header: 'Acupuncture' },
  { key: 'limits', header: 'Typical Limits' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', altMedicine: 'Yes', chiropractic: 'Covered', acupuncture: 'Covered', limits: '$1,000-2,500/year' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', altMedicine: 'Yes', chiropractic: 'Covered', acupuncture: 'Covered', limits: '$1,500-3,000/year' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', altMedicine: 'Some plans', chiropractic: 'Some plans', acupuncture: 'Some plans', limits: '$500-1,500/year' },
  { provider: 'Aetna International', altMedicine: 'Limited', chiropractic: 'Limited', acupuncture: 'Limited', limits: 'Varies' },
  { provider: 'IMG Global', altMedicine: 'No', chiropractic: 'No', acupuncture: 'No', limits: 'N/A' },
];

const treatmentColumns = [
  { key: 'treatment', header: 'Treatment Type' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Typical Coverage' },
  { key: 'notes', header: 'Notes' },
];

const treatmentRows = [
  { treatment: 'Chiropractic', coverage: 'Often covered', notes: 'Session limits common (20-30/year)' },
  { treatment: 'Acupuncture', coverage: 'Often covered', notes: 'Licensed practitioners required' },
  { treatment: 'Osteopathy', coverage: 'Usually covered', notes: 'Similar to chiropractic coverage' },
  { treatment: 'Physiotherapy', coverage: 'Typically covered', notes: 'Often under standard outpatient' },
  { treatment: 'Homeopathy', coverage: 'Sometimes covered', notes: 'Less common, premium plans' },
  { treatment: 'Naturopathy', coverage: 'Rarely covered', notes: 'Limited availability' },
  { treatment: 'Traditional Chinese Medicine', coverage: 'Sometimes covered', notes: 'Varies by region and plan' },
  { treatment: 'Ayurveda', coverage: 'Rarely covered', notes: 'Very limited coverage' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Expat Insurance for Alternative Medicine 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance with alternative medicine coverage. Find plans that cover chiropractic, acupuncture, osteopathy, and complementary therapies abroad."
  headline="Best Expat Insurance for Alternative Medicine"
  subheadline="Looking for coverage beyond conventional medicine? Here are the international health plans that include chiropractic, acupuncture, and complementary therapies."
  heroImage="/images/answers/best-alternative-medicine-insurance.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  showHeroCta={false}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Plans"
  ctaButtonHref="/compare/"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Top Picks for Alternative Medicine</h2>
  <p>
    These insurers offer the best coverage for complementary and alternative medicine:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🌿</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Alternative Medicine Coverage</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Comprehensive complementary therapy coverage including chiropractic, acupuncture, and osteopathy.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">💆</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Overall Wellness</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Strong alternative medicine benefits as part of comprehensive wellness coverage.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🇪🇺</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best European Coverage</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Good alternative medicine options on European-focused plans.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">⚠️</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Important Note</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Limited Coverage</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Most plans have annual limits ($500-3,000) and session caps for alternative therapies.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="what-is-covered">What Alternative Medicine Coverage Means</h2>
  <p>
    Alternative medicine coverage in international health insurance typically includes:
  </p>

  <h3>Commonly Covered Therapies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Chiropractic:</strong> Spinal manipulation and musculoskeletal treatment</li>
    <li><strong>Acupuncture:</strong> Traditional needle therapy for various conditions</li>
    <li><strong>Osteopathy:</strong> Manual therapy focusing on musculoskeletal system</li>
    <li><strong>Physiotherapy:</strong> Often included in standard outpatient coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Sometimes Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Homeopathy</li>
    <li>Traditional Chinese Medicine (TCM)</li>
    <li>Naturopathy</li>
    <li>Massage therapy (therapeutic)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Rarely Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Ayurveda</li>
    <li>Aromatherapy</li>
    <li>Crystal healing</li>
    <li>Reiki and energy therapies</li>
    <li>Unproven or experimental treatments</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Holistic Health Coverage"
    description="Compare plans that cover complementary and alternative therapies."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Alternative Medicine Coverage Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global — Best Alternative Medicine Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers comprehensive complementary therapy benefits.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Chiropractic care covered</li>
    <li>Acupuncture included</li>
    <li>Osteopathy covered</li>
    <li>Annual limits typically $1,000-2,500</li>
    <li>Licensed practitioner requirement</li>
    <li>Combined with standard outpatient benefits</li>
    <li>Good network of practitioners</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Annual and session limits apply. Best coverage on comprehensive plans. Verify specific therapies before treatment.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our full Cigna Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Bupa Global — Comprehensive Wellness Approach</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global includes alternative medicine as part of overall wellness benefits.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Alternative therapies included</li>
    <li>Chiropractic and acupuncture covered</li>
    <li>Higher limits on premium plans ($1,500-3,000)</li>
    <li>Part of holistic wellness program</li>
    <li>Good practitioner network</li>
    <li>Osteopathy covered</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Premium pricing. Best alternative medicine on higher-tier plans. Limits still apply.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/bupa-global">Read our full Bupa Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Allianz Care — European Alternative Medicine</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers alternative medicine coverage on select plans.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Coverage on some plans</li>
    <li>Chiropractic and acupuncture options</li>
    <li>Good European practitioner network</li>
    <li>Competitive pricing</li>
    <li>Osteopathy included on some plans</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Not all plans include alternative medicine. Lower limits than leaders. Verify coverage before enrolling.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/allianz-care">Read our full Allianz Care review</a></p>

  <h2 id="treatment-types">Treatment Types Explained</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={treatmentColumns} rows={treatmentRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Chiropractic Care</h3>
  <p>
    The most commonly covered alternative therapy:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Focus on spine and musculoskeletal system</li>
    <li>Manual adjustments and manipulation</li>
    <li>Often covered for back pain, neck pain, headaches</li>
    <li>Typical limits: 20-30 sessions per year</li>
    <li>Must be licensed chiropractor</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Acupuncture</h3>
  <p>
    Traditional Chinese needle therapy:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Used for pain management, stress, various conditions</li>
    <li>Increasingly covered by international insurers</li>
    <li>Must be performed by licensed acupuncturist</li>
    <li>Session limits typically apply</li>
    <li>Popular in Asia, growing globally</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Osteopathy</h3>
  <p>
    Manual therapy approach:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Focus on musculoskeletal system</li>
    <li>Similar coverage to chiropractic</li>
    <li>More common in Europe</li>
    <li>Licensed osteopath required</li>
    <li>Often combined with other manual therapies</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Traditional Chinese Medicine</h3>
  <p>
    Beyond acupuncture:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Includes herbal medicine, cupping, moxibustion</li>
    <li>Coverage varies significantly</li>
    <li>More common in plans sold in Asia</li>
    <li>Licensed TCM practitioner required</li>
    <li>Herbal medicines may not be covered</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Find Your Coverage"
    description="Alternative medicine coverage varies—compare specific benefits."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
  />

  <h2 id="considerations">Key Considerations</h2>

  <h3>Annual and Session Limits</h3>
  <p>
    Almost all alternative medicine coverage has limits:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Annual dollar limits: typically $500-3,000</li>
    <li>Session limits: often 20-30 visits per year</li>
    <li>May combine all alternative therapies into one limit</li>
    <li>Premium plans have higher limits</li>
    <li>Calculate if limits meet your expected usage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Practitioner Requirements</h3>
  <p>
    Coverage requires licensed practitioners:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Must be licensed/registered in their field</li>
    <li>Credentials verified for coverage</li>
    <li>Treatment from unqualified providers not covered</li>
    <li>Some countries have different licensing standards</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Medical Necessity</h3>
  <p>
    Some insurers require medical justification:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>May need referral from primary doctor</li>
    <li>Treatment must be for covered condition</li>
    <li>Wellness or preventive may not qualify</li>
    <li>Check specific requirements</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Regional Variations</h3>
  <p>
    Alternative medicine coverage and availability varies:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>More common on European and Asian plans</li>
    <li>US plans more restrictive</li>
    <li>Practitioner availability varies by location</li>
    <li>Some therapies more accepted in certain regions</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is chiropractic care covered by international health insurance?</h3>
  <p>
    Often yes, on comprehensive plans from major insurers like Cigna and Bupa. Coverage typically has session limits (20-30/year) and annual dollar caps ($1,000-3,000). Budget plans usually exclude chiropractic. Always verify before treatment.
  </p>

  <h3>Does insurance cover acupuncture abroad?</h3>
  <p>
    Many international health plans cover acupuncture, especially those sold in or covering Asia. Must be performed by a licensed acupuncturist. Session limits and annual caps typically apply. Check your specific plan for coverage details.
  </p>

  <h3>Are homeopathy and naturopathy covered?</h3>
  <p>
    Rarely. Some premium plans in Europe may include limited homeopathy coverage. Naturopathy is seldom covered by international health insurance. These are typically considered "unproven" by insurers and excluded.
  </p>

  <h3>Do I need a referral for alternative medicine?</h3>
  <p>
    Depends on your plan. Some require referral from a primary care physician. Others allow direct access to chiropractors and acupuncturists. Pre-authorization may be needed for ongoing treatment. Check your policy requirements.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use any alternative medicine practitioner?</h3>
  <p>
    The practitioner must be licensed/registered in their field. In-network practitioners may offer direct billing. Out-of-network is usually covered but requires reimbursement claims. Credentials will be verified before payment.
  </p>

  <h3>Why are annual limits so low for alternative medicine?</h3>
  <p>
    Insurers view many alternative therapies as supplementary rather than essential care. Limits control costs while still offering the benefit. If you rely heavily on alternative medicine, budget for out-of-pocket costs beyond insurance limits.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This content is for informational purposes only. Alternative medicine coverage varies significantly by plan and insurer. We are not insurance brokers or medical professionals. Always verify specific coverage directly with insurers.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
